column4: Hello everyone. Installed Ubuntu 12.10 days ago and software updater tells me every day my computer is up to date, but it has only updated 3 or 4 packages since install. Is anyone else experiencing this?
shouldnt be an issue. If you really want to be sure do "sudo aptitude update" in a terminal
and then see if software center wants to upgrade thigns
do I just paste that whole line into terminal? Tried it, but not doing anything
are you running 12.10? Have you noticed the same thing at all?
I am just trying to check if your ubuntu points at the right repositories. I am running something else...
sudo gedit /etc/apt/sources.list and paste wahts int eh file to pastebing please.
everything else you said I understand, but what is pastebin?
http://pastebin.com/ hit submit, then give me the link. its a text sharing website
youa re good. your system should be up to date.
Thanks. Weird. Have a good one!
